WEBVTT

00:02.440 --> 00:03.589
<i>Previously on</i> The O.C.<i>:</i>

00:03.760 --> 00:05.910
Julie and Caleb's wedding invitation.
Getting married in...

00:06.080 --> 00:07.911
- Two weeks.
- Wow. They're really doing it. 

00:08.080 --> 00:10.355
I know it should be simple.
Your boyfriend hits you...

00:10.520 --> 00:12.590
...you leave him. Right?
- It's never simple.

00:12.760 --> 00:16.389
You're probably a fan of the classics.
Superman? No? Batman?

00:16.560 --> 00:20.155
You probably really need Ryan right now.
Me being here, I'm getting in the way.

00:20.320 --> 00:22.754
- It's more than twice what we put into it.
- Caught me at a good time.

00:22.920 --> 00:26.151
- He's up to something.
- I don't care. $2.5 million.

00:26.320 --> 00:28.151
You and me, we're gonna be fine.

00:33.440 --> 00:35.032
Ryan.

00:35.200 --> 00:37.714
Ryan, hey. Hey, man, are you asleep?

00:42.920 --> 00:44.114
Ryan.

00:45.360 --> 00:48.875
Ryan. Are you asleep?
Yeah, I can't sleep either.

00:49.040 --> 00:52.919
I know what you're gonna say. You know,
she hasn't technically dumped me yet...

00:53.080 --> 00:55.640
...but it's only a matter of time, right?
So, what do I do?

00:55.800 --> 00:58.155
Do I force a confrontation
or do I just continue...

00:58.320 --> 01:01.915
...to be whiny and passive-aggressive
until she realizes what a catch I am?

01:02.840 --> 01:04.034
Ryan?

01:04.200 --> 01:06.634
- Ryan, Ryan, Ryan. You asleep?
- Yeah.

01:06.800 --> 01:08.870
Sorry.
I'm gonna let you go back to sleep, okay?

01:09.160 --> 01:11.549
As bad as things are for me,
they're worse for you.

01:11.720 --> 01:12.709
What?

01:12.880 --> 01:16.236
I'm at least in my own bed not sleeping.
You're on my floor not sleeping.

01:16.400 --> 01:19.597
- Because you won't stop talking.
- But also because your ex-girlfriend...

01:19.760 --> 01:22.752
...is sleeping in your room,
to the dismay of your girlfriend.

01:22.920 --> 01:24.956
- Marissa's fine with it.
- I'm sure she is.

01:25.120 --> 01:28.237
The same way you'd be fine with it if
Oliver was sleeping on her couch.

01:28.400 --> 01:29.389
It's cool.

01:29.560 --> 01:31.312
What, you want me to kick Theresa out?

01:31.480 --> 01:34.677
No. But aren't you just the least bit
curious as to when she's leaving?

01:34.840 --> 01:36.592
No, I'm not. I'm not worried about it.

01:36.760 --> 01:37.795
- Okay.
- Okay.

01:37.960 --> 01:41.396
Good. Night. Go back to bed.
Or the floor.

01:43.000 --> 01:49.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:52.440 --> 01:54.715
- I should talk to Theresa.
- Let me come with you.

01:57.920 --> 02:00.514
- Theresa?
- Housekeeping.

02:00.680 --> 02:03.638
- Hello?
- Maybe she's still at work.

02:03.800 --> 02:06.314
- Her bag's here.
- Yeah. Apparently, she's been shopping.

02:09.880 --> 02:11.836
Sorry. I didn't hear you guys come in.

02:12.000 --> 02:15.197
Let me know if you ever need anything.
My mom's got lots of toiletries.

02:16.400 --> 02:19.949
Thanks, but I'm probably not
gonna be here that much longer.

02:20.320 --> 02:22.117
You're not?

02:22.280 --> 02:25.113
No, I can't impose
on Seth's parents forever.

02:25.280 --> 02:26.918
- Sure you can. I intend to.
- Thanks...

02:27.080 --> 02:31.153
...but I really need to figure things out.
I have some family I can call, so...

02:33.240 --> 02:35.356
So see you tomorrow?

02:35.520 --> 02:37.875
No. I picked up a morning shift
at the bakery, so...

02:38.040 --> 02:40.190
Oh, all right. So maybe after school?

02:41.000 --> 02:45.391
- Sure. But aren't you and Marissa...?
- Yeah. No, I mean we'll both see you.

02:45.560 --> 02:49.792
We'll all see you, because my girlfriend's
currently dating her father, which to me...

02:49.960 --> 02:52.076
- Seth.
- We'll talk about this tomorrow.

02:52.240 --> 02:54.151
- Good night.
- Good night.

02:55.640 --> 02:57.517
All right, good night.

02:57.880 --> 02:59.108
Night.

03:51.640 --> 03:54.996
So, what's it gonna be, Cal?
The Hyatt Newporter?

03:55.160 --> 03:57.993
The pool at the Four Seasons Hotel
where everybody gets married?

03:58.160 --> 04:00.754
Or the beautiful glass cathedral
overlooking the ocean...

04:00.920 --> 04:02.558
...at the Wayfarer's Chapel?

04:06.120 --> 04:08.315
I have to get to work.

04:08.480 --> 04:10.994
Whatever you like, Juju.

04:12.240 --> 04:13.468
Sorry about breakfast, Kiki.

04:13.640 --> 04:17.474
Dad, the only reason we're having
this breakfast is so we can do some work.

04:17.640 --> 04:20.438
You have been so busy with the wedding,
I haven't even seen you.

04:20.600 --> 04:24.593
Every time I've asked him to help me
with the wedding, he says he's with you.

04:24.760 --> 04:27.797
Really? So, CayCay,
what have you been doing all this time?

04:27.960 --> 04:29.393
Don't you have someplace to be?

04:29.560 --> 04:31.835
As a matter of fact,
I'm meeting Jimmy for breakfast.

04:32.000 --> 04:34.309
I bet even that sounds pretty good
to you right now.

04:34.480 --> 04:36.118
The Wayfarer Chapel it is.

04:36.280 --> 04:39.955
Well, are you sure? I mean, these photos
don't really do it justice. You know what?

04:40.120 --> 04:42.714
I should take you up there this weekend,
you'll love it.

04:42.880 --> 04:44.598
I wish I could. I'm out of town.

04:44.760 --> 04:47.672
What? Since when? You can't go.
We're getting married next week.

04:47.840 --> 04:50.035
Just one night. Business.

04:50.200 --> 04:52.236
Business where?

04:52.400 --> 04:55.358
- Nevada.
- Nevada. As in Las Vegas, Nevada?

04:55.720 --> 04:58.188
- Actually...
- You're going out of town for one night...

04:58.360 --> 05:00.920
...to Vegas on business? What business?

05:01.080 --> 05:02.229
There is no business.

05:02.400 --> 05:05.392
You're going to Vegas
because you're having a bachelor party.

05:05.560 --> 05:07.869
- Some of the investors and I are...
- Hiring strippers...

05:08.040 --> 05:11.510
...drinking too much and gambling all
night the weekend before our wedding?

05:11.680 --> 05:14.274
It sounds like a bachelor party to me.

05:14.440 --> 05:17.398
I have to admit,
I feel a little hurt that I wasn't invited.

05:17.560 --> 05:19.994
- Yeah, me too.
- Not that I have any affection for you.

05:20.160 --> 05:22.833
You know that. But I do love the Vegas.

05:23.000 --> 05:26.515
- I didn't know you love the Vegas, Dad.
- I love the Vegas. I love the Vegas.

05:26.680 --> 05:28.352
Ryan, how do you feel about the Vegas?

05:28.520 --> 05:30.829
Never been to the Vegas.
Mom was all about the Reno.

05:31.000 --> 05:34.037
Dad, we should go. You love Vegas.
Ryan and I have never been.

05:34.200 --> 05:37.112
He can use his mutant
card-counting abilities to pay for the trip.

05:37.280 --> 05:40.158
- Sounds like fun for the whole family.
- What about Theresa?

05:40.320 --> 05:42.754
Well, I can take care of Theresa.
You guys should go.

05:42.920 --> 05:45.070
Do I have any say in this?

05:45.240 --> 05:46.559
No.

05:47.160 --> 05:49.071
Enjoy your bachelor party.

06:00.000 --> 06:01.592
Hey. Ready for breakfast?

06:01.760 --> 06:04.911
Almost. My realtor is on her way.
I just have to give her the contract.

06:05.080 --> 06:06.229
Contract for what?

06:06.400 --> 06:07.958
Well, with any luck...

06:09.160 --> 06:10.513
...my new house.

06:11.120 --> 06:13.156
Jimmy, it's right on the beach.
It's perfect.

06:13.320 --> 06:16.039
I want to give Marissa a home
she can be proud of. You know?

06:16.200 --> 06:18.350
What are you gonna do
with your half of Caleb's money?

06:18.520 --> 06:20.351
I'm taking some of it
to Vegas this weekend.

06:20.520 --> 06:23.751
The boys and I are crashing
his bachelor party. You want to come?

06:23.920 --> 06:27.629
Are you kidding? The man bailed us out,
took Julie off my hands.

06:27.800 --> 06:29.279
I'll buy him his first lap dance.

06:29.640 --> 06:34.270
Hell, I'll give him one myself. Can you
grab that? I just gotta get the contract.

06:37.080 --> 06:39.435
Hi. Gail van Deepen. You must be Sandy.

06:39.600 --> 06:41.670
- Yeah.
- Congratulations on selling the restaurant.

06:41.840 --> 06:43.114
You must have made a fortune.

06:43.280 --> 06:46.477
I heard Robert Campbell is gonna turn
that area into an outdoor mall.

06:46.640 --> 06:49.234
Robert Campbell?
We sold the restaurant to Caleb Nichol.

06:49.400 --> 06:53.234
Then I guess Caleb is gonna make
a fortune. Well, another fortune, right?

06:53.400 --> 06:57.313
But you and Jimmy must have made good
money. What are you gonna do next?

06:58.400 --> 07:00.038
I wanna kill him.

07:00.200 --> 07:02.589
Then I'd probably go to jail,
but it would be better...

07:02.760 --> 07:05.149
...than having to move in
with him and my mom, right?

07:05.320 --> 07:07.629
That way, I won't have to tell my dad
I'm moving out.

07:07.800 --> 07:09.233
You still haven't told him?

07:10.040 --> 07:12.270
What am I supposed to say,
that Caleb's blackmailing me?

07:12.440 --> 07:14.908
My dad'll kill him
and I'll have to move in with my mom.

07:15.080 --> 07:16.559
So, what are you gonna tell him?

07:17.040 --> 07:19.952
I don't know, but I guess
I have to do it by this weekend, huh?

07:20.120 --> 07:22.190
Your dad might be going
to Vegas this weekend.

07:22.360 --> 07:23.873
How do you know?

07:24.280 --> 07:26.430
Because I might be going
to Vegas this weekend.

07:26.600 --> 07:27.874
For what?

07:28.040 --> 07:29.712
- Caleb's bachelor party.
- What?

07:29.880 --> 07:32.952
With, like, strippers and prostitutes
and showgirls?

07:33.120 --> 07:35.429
I don't know, I hope so.
What? No. I'm not gonna go.

07:35.600 --> 07:37.397
I can't leave Theresa here by herself.

07:37.560 --> 07:39.471
Theresa? What about me?

07:40.560 --> 07:43.028
You know what I mean.
You got Summer and your sister.

07:43.200 --> 07:44.952
Theresa, she's got nobody.

07:45.400 --> 07:46.958
Well, she's got me.

07:47.480 --> 07:50.517
I mean, I am your girlfriend, right?

07:52.440 --> 07:56.274
So, I mean, any friend of yours
is a friend of mine.

07:56.440 --> 07:57.998
Right?

08:03.760 --> 08:06.638
- You are my girlfriend.
- Glad to hear it.

08:08.160 --> 08:12.278
- Now, about those strippers...
- What strippers? I don't know of any stri...

08:12.440 --> 08:14.829
I don't want Chippendales.
I want strippers.

08:15.000 --> 08:17.878
Full-on, full-frontal male strippers.

08:18.040 --> 08:20.793
Preferably at a place
that serves bottomless margaritas.

08:21.880 --> 08:24.713
Or I could invite the girls over
and I could throw you...

08:24.880 --> 08:27.314
...a lovely,
catered bachelorette cocktail party.

08:27.480 --> 08:29.914
- With strippers.
- Without strippers.

08:30.080 --> 08:32.594
Julie, we are smart, sophisticated women.

08:32.760 --> 08:37.231
We don't need strange, naked men
dancing in front of us to be entertained.

08:39.840 --> 08:42.957
I'm not as smart as you.
Plus, the boys are getting strippers.

08:43.120 --> 08:45.076
The boys are not getting strippers.

08:45.240 --> 08:48.994
Kirsten, it's Las Vegas. You get strippers
as a side with your entr Áe.

08:49.520 --> 08:52.671
They're getting strippers. Why else
would Sandy go to Vegas with Caleb?

08:52.840 --> 08:54.159
Strippers, huh?

08:54.320 --> 08:56.390
Get all the Newpsies into limos,
drive to L. A...

08:56.560 --> 08:58.835
...have dinner on Sunset,
then head south to Mantopia.

08:59.000 --> 09:00.991
- Or the Stud Farm.
- You've done research.

09:01.160 --> 09:04.835
Todd in Accounting, who also told me
about this place called The Petting Zoo.

09:05.000 --> 09:06.558
It's not exactly legal, but...

09:06.720 --> 09:09.553
Julie, I am not going to a place
called The Petting Zoo.

09:09.720 --> 09:11.358
You don't know where the pets
have been.

09:11.560 --> 09:12.993
We'll be too drunk to care.

09:13.160 --> 09:17.073
- No strippers.
- Just one stripper? Please?

09:17.240 --> 09:19.800
Just one little stripper
who never hurt anyone...

09:19.960 --> 09:22.349
...who's just trying to make his way
in the world?

09:22.840 --> 09:24.512
Naked.

09:24.680 --> 09:26.352
One little stripper.

09:26.720 --> 09:27.994
Yes! You're the best.

09:29.120 --> 09:30.838
But no Chippendales.

09:31.160 --> 09:33.151
And not little.

09:34.520 --> 09:35.714
A bachelor party?

09:36.280 --> 09:38.840
Where really anything could happen.

09:39.520 --> 09:40.714
Good to know.

09:40.880 --> 09:42.791
Yeah. Just kind of
a courtesy thing, really.

09:42.960 --> 09:46.077
Seeing as how, last time I checked,
we're still boyfriend and girlfriend.

09:46.240 --> 09:50.552
Even though you've been ignoring me in
the halls and don't return any of my calls.

09:50.720 --> 09:52.358
I didn't mean for that to rhyme.

09:52.960 --> 09:54.916
- Look, Cohen...
- I just want you to tell me...

09:55.080 --> 09:58.197
...that you're not gonna let
what your dad thinks of me break us up.

10:04.000 --> 10:05.638
- He's my dad.
- So what?

10:05.800 --> 10:09.839
Summer, I don't care about your dad.
Okay? I care about you a lot.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.956
And if that's not good enough for you...

10:13.760 --> 10:16.718
Obviously, that's not good enough
for you, so I'll go to Vegas.

10:18.840 --> 10:20.353
Wait.

10:25.160 --> 10:27.116
- Hi.
- Hey.

10:27.280 --> 10:28.918
How was work? How you feeling?

10:29.080 --> 10:33.073
Good. I'm actually going back.
I picked up another shift tonight.

10:33.240 --> 10:36.118
Marissa and I were kind of hoping
we could all hang out.

10:36.520 --> 10:40.593
Yeah, I can't. I have to make money
if I'm gonna go to Atlanta.

10:41.040 --> 10:43.952
- Atlanta?
- Yeah, my cousin Kim lives in Atlanta.

10:44.120 --> 10:46.839
She said I can go stay with her
as long as I pay my own way.

10:48.960 --> 10:52.077
I mean, she doesn't have
a pool house or anything...

10:52.360 --> 10:54.954
...but that way,
maybe I can get a second chance too.

10:57.800 --> 10:59.597
How much you need?

11:05.080 --> 11:06.229
I can't take your money.

11:08.960 --> 11:12.236
- I don't even... Two thousand dollars?
- I'll ask the Cohens.

11:12.400 --> 11:13.674
No, you won't.

11:14.320 --> 11:17.118
Listen to me.
This is not your problem, okay?

11:17.760 --> 11:20.433
Go. Win. Make money.

11:20.600 --> 11:22.192
That's what I'm gonna do.

11:30.680 --> 11:32.591
Two thousand dollars, huh?

11:32.760 --> 11:34.830
Well, I've got about...

11:35.000 --> 11:38.515
I'd say I've got about a thousand
in savings bonds, bar mitzvah bucks.

11:38.680 --> 11:40.272
I could throw in a couple hundred.

11:40.440 --> 11:41.919
I can't ask you guys to do that.

11:42.080 --> 11:43.672
You didn't ask. We volunteered.

11:44.280 --> 11:45.872
Thanks, but it's still not enough.

11:46.040 --> 11:49.476
You could make it enough. Take that
money to Vegas and triple it at blackjack.

11:49.640 --> 11:52.279
It's been a while
since I've done the card-counting thing.

11:52.440 --> 11:55.989
Listen, I'm gonna start you off slow.
If you suck, I'm just gonna cut you off.

11:57.280 --> 12:00.477
- How do we get in the casinos?
- I think we'd use our fake IDs.

12:00.640 --> 12:03.438
- You have fake IDs?
- C.D. Sebulski, it's good to meet you.

12:03.600 --> 12:06.034
- Have you met Marty Nayfis?
- Oh, God.

12:07.080 --> 12:10.550
Okay, look, you guys go to Vegas.
I'll take care of Theresa.

12:10.720 --> 12:15.396
If you win, great. If not,
well, then Theresa never has to know.

12:16.760 --> 12:19.752
- What do you have to lose?
- Just $ 1000 in bar mitzvah bonds.

12:19.920 --> 12:21.512
But other than that, nothing.

12:21.880 --> 12:23.518
You in?

12:24.000 --> 12:26.195
Marty, are you in?

12:29.200 --> 12:30.349
I'm in.

12:56.120 --> 12:59.237
- I love the Vegas.
- Reno was never like this.

13:07.120 --> 13:08.599
What is this place?

13:08.760 --> 13:13.231
This is the Hard Rock Hotel and Casino.
According to Seth, it's ground zero...

13:13.400 --> 13:15.516
...for aging hipsters like yourself.

13:16.920 --> 13:18.512
I thought we were going to Caesar's.

13:18.680 --> 13:21.194
Caesar's didn't have
a permanent Springsteen exhibit.

13:21.360 --> 13:23.112
Although they do have Celine Dion.

13:23.280 --> 13:24.679
Yet another reason we're here.

13:24.840 --> 13:28.435
- Mock if you must, but she can sing.
- You're gonna regret saying that...

13:28.600 --> 13:30.670
...on your birthday.
- Yeah, really.

13:30.840 --> 13:32.592
Welcome to Hard Rock.
My name is Amy.

13:32.760 --> 13:34.478
Which one of you is Mr. Cohen?

13:34.640 --> 13:37.200
Hi, Amy, we spoke on the phone.
It's good to see you.

13:37.360 --> 13:40.238
Yes, good to see you. We have
the penthouse all ready for you.

13:40.400 --> 13:41.674
If you will follow me.

13:41.840 --> 13:43.831
- Penthouse?
- Yeah.

13:44.000 --> 13:46.798
- So whose card did you put that on?
- Oh, please, the old man's.

13:46.960 --> 13:48.791
Oh, I love you, son. I love you.

13:48.960 --> 13:50.473
I love you too, Dad.

13:51.120 --> 13:52.838
Just not as much as I love Vegas.

13:53.000 --> 13:55.673
The casino, restaurants, pool and spa
are all on this level.

13:55.840 --> 13:58.308
And if you'll follow me,
I'll show you our bowling alley.

13:58.480 --> 13:59.959
God, there's a bowling alley?

14:00.120 --> 14:02.634
Yes, sir. It's in your room.

14:03.960 --> 14:05.154
Did you see that?

14:05.320 --> 14:08.039
I just almost bowled a strike.

14:08.520 --> 14:11.273
In our hotel room, man.
I'm never going home.

14:16.200 --> 14:17.952
It's like a million-dollar frat house.

14:18.120 --> 14:20.509
I know. It's fantastic.

14:21.360 --> 14:23.191
Well, I'm gonna explore the casino.

14:23.360 --> 14:24.998
May I give you gentlemen a tour?

14:25.160 --> 14:26.752
No, I'll find my way. Thanks.

14:26.920 --> 14:29.559
- We're good. Thanks, Amy.
- Thanks.

14:30.800 --> 14:34.270
Actually, you know what?
We'll take that tour.

14:34.960 --> 14:37.315
Sure. I just need to see some ID.

14:38.440 --> 14:41.955
It's just a formality. We have
a lot of kids under 21 using fake IDs...

14:42.120 --> 14:46.352
...to get onto the casino floor. We'd hate
to have to throw them out of the hotel.

14:46.880 --> 14:49.348
You know what? I don't think
we're gonna need that tour.

14:49.520 --> 14:51.431
- But thank you for stopping by.
- Absolutely.

14:51.600 --> 14:53.033
Really sweet.

14:56.360 --> 14:59.557
What are we gonna do? I don't
wanna get thrown out. I love the hotel.

14:59.720 --> 15:01.312
- Me too.
- I wanna marry the hotel...

15:01.480 --> 15:03.391
...and have gambling-addicted,
alcoholic kids.

15:03.560 --> 15:05.835
- We'll find another casino.
- What, a youth casino?

15:07.320 --> 15:08.514
Seth, it's Vegas.

15:08.680 --> 15:12.036
You wanna find some action in this town,
all you gotta do is ask.

15:14.480 --> 15:16.311
Winner. Pay the line.

15:19.360 --> 15:21.078
Yeah.

15:22.320 --> 15:24.117
Where are we doing this?

15:25.040 --> 15:28.555
No, I'm at the Hard Rock, of all places.

15:28.720 --> 15:29.914
Fine.

15:30.080 --> 15:31.399
I'm on my cell.

15:31.560 --> 15:35.599
- So where's the party?
- There is no party, just a quiet dinner.

15:35.760 --> 15:38.228
Hey, have you figured out what
you're gonna do with the restaurant?

15:38.400 --> 15:41.233
Not yet. You figured out
what you're gonna do with that money...

15:41.400 --> 15:42.992
...that I paid you for it?

15:43.160 --> 15:45.230
I'm putting all mine on the hard ways.

15:45.400 --> 15:48.198
Jimmy's gonna buy a house
for himself and Marissa.

15:49.480 --> 15:50.708
Really?

15:51.960 --> 15:55.350
Last time I talked to Marissa,
she was planning on moving in with us.

16:03.680 --> 16:06.240
- <i>ever gonna stop being mad at me, Ada?</i>

16:06.840 --> 16:10.594
I'm sorry, but does it strike anyone else
as tragic that the boys are in Las Vegas...

16:10.760 --> 16:14.309
...doing God knows what, while we sit
here watching <i>The Valley</i> marathon?

16:14.480 --> 16:17.313
Hey, it's Summ's favorite show, okay?

16:17.480 --> 16:18.913
Right, Summ?

16:19.080 --> 16:21.355
- Are you crying?
- No.

16:23.000 --> 16:25.275
It's a sad episode.

16:28.520 --> 16:30.112
- She broke up with Seth.
- Coop.

