- How is the food here?
- Filet's excellent.

35:16.040 --> 35:17.837
- Really?
- Would you care to join us?

35:18.000 --> 35:20.230
- Actually, we should just...
- Don't mind if I do.

35:20.400 --> 35:23.995
So I understand that you're interested
in Caleb's Balboa coastline property.

35:24.680 --> 35:27.877
I can see why. It is the perfect location.

35:28.040 --> 35:30.838
You mind? I'm parched.

35:31.680 --> 35:35.673
As a matter of fact, some partners and I
recently tried to open a restaurant there.

35:35.840 --> 35:39.549
Not unlike this one, except we had
two kinds of meat loaf and dirty martinis.

35:40.320 --> 35:43.312
The problem was,
we could not get a liquor license...

35:43.640 --> 35:46.552
...and for the longest time,
we couldn't figure out why.

35:46.720 --> 35:49.109
- Sandy, this is not the time.
- You gonna eat that?

35:49.280 --> 35:52.477
Turns out, one of our partners
went behind our backs...

35:52.640 --> 35:56.349
...to a friend on the city council and
got them to deny us the liquor license.

35:56.520 --> 35:58.476
So he bought us out,
and now he's peddling...

35:58.640 --> 36:02.474
...that piece of property
at a much higher price to someone else.

36:02.640 --> 36:06.155
- Robert, I have to ask you to excuse us.
- The problem is, the joke's on him.

36:06.920 --> 36:10.708
Not only is he guilty of collusion
and fraud, but he and his property...

36:10.880 --> 36:13.633
...are going to be tied up
in civil litigation for months.

36:13.960 --> 36:15.951
Years, if I have anything to say about it.

36:17.320 --> 36:22.155
The bottom line: That coastline property,
it's absolutely worthless.

36:23.000 --> 36:24.592
What do you think of that?

36:24.760 --> 36:27.149
- I have to ask you to leave.
- Hands off! You wanna go?

36:27.320 --> 36:30.949
- We'll go. Come on. I'll take you...
- Sandy, don't. Let me.

36:33.000 --> 36:35.878
You think you can manipulate me?!
Hold my daughter hostage?!

36:36.040 --> 36:38.554
Easy, easy. What are you doing?
You beat me to the punch.

36:38.720 --> 36:41.837
We'll see you back in Newport, Dad.
Come on. Go, go.

36:54.080 --> 36:55.399
Five hundred. You got nothing.

37:01.080 --> 37:02.229
I'm out.

37:08.120 --> 37:10.156
- I need you to lend me some money.
- What?

37:10.320 --> 37:13.756
No. No way. You just lost, like, $3000.
There's no way I'm lending you money.

37:13.920 --> 37:15.433
Then I guess you don't get paid.

37:15.760 --> 37:19.389
Look, this is not a game, okay? You
and your friends could get seriously hurt.

37:19.560 --> 37:20.834
Yeah, whose fault is that?

37:21.320 --> 37:22.514
I was just doing my job.

37:22.680 --> 37:25.478
You guys were staying in the penthouse.
I thought you had money.

37:26.720 --> 37:30.076
I don't understand.
This afternoon you were doing so good.

37:30.640 --> 37:31.834
Now you suck.

37:33.440 --> 37:36.796
So I guess Angry Trucker Hat's
feeling pretty confident right now.

37:38.880 --> 37:40.393
Wouldn't you say?

37:43.560 --> 37:44.913
You lost on purpose?

37:45.080 --> 37:47.196
I won a lot of money this afternoon.

37:47.720 --> 37:49.438
Now I need yours.

38:01.160 --> 38:02.752
Deal me in.

38:04.640 --> 38:06.790
I can't believe he gave you
his angry trucker hat.

38:06.960 --> 38:08.473
He didn't give it to me, I won it.

38:08.640 --> 38:10.039
That's not really winning then.

38:10.200 --> 38:13.397
Be nice, Cohen.
He paid off your pimps and your ho's.

38:13.560 --> 38:16.552
Yeah. I did lose
your bar mitzvah money, though. Sorry.

38:16.720 --> 38:19.678
I lost my bar mitzvah money, okay?
And I also lost Theresa's money...

38:19.840 --> 38:22.957
...which is the only reason you came.
- No, it's not the only reason.

38:23.120 --> 38:25.475
- You don't think the trip's a total waste?
- No, no.

38:25.640 --> 38:29.110
We won some, we lost some. We're
walking out of Vegas pretty much even.

38:29.280 --> 38:32.033
I'd say some of us
are walking out ahead.

38:33.760 --> 38:36.991
I think if it were up to you,
we wouldn't be walking out of here at all.

38:37.160 --> 38:40.357
- Now we have a good Vegas story.
- I don't think you wanna tell people...

38:40.520 --> 38:43.432
...that you lost your bar mitzvah money
on prostitutes.

38:43.840 --> 38:47.196
Yeah, well, you know what they say,
what happens in Vegas, stays in Vegas.

38:47.360 --> 38:50.875
- I thought that was Tijuana.
- I think that hat should stay in Vegas.

38:53.560 --> 38:54.834
Sorry.

39:04.240 --> 39:06.117
Definitely love the Vegas.

39:28.560 --> 39:30.039
How was Vegas?

39:31.440 --> 39:33.431
Definitely a spectacle.

39:33.600 --> 39:35.397
How were the strippers?

39:36.000 --> 39:39.629
- Surprisingly tame, actually.
- That's good.

39:40.680 --> 39:42.318
Considering what happened next.

39:43.120 --> 39:44.917
- Do I want to know?
- Depends.

39:45.120 --> 39:48.430
- What is it?
- On how you feel about drunken catfights.

39:48.840 --> 39:50.353
Julie and Hailey?

39:50.520 --> 39:53.557
Wow. Even Vegas can't compete
with that.

39:54.080 --> 39:56.594
So how did it go with my dad?

39:57.360 --> 40:01.273
Well, you'll be relieved to know
I did not punch him in the mouth.

40:01.440 --> 40:02.714
That is a relief.

40:03.280 --> 40:04.633
Jimmy did.

40:05.880 --> 40:08.952
I don't think we'll be invited back
to the Hard Rock. But you know what?

40:09.120 --> 40:11.714
I'm not really looking forward
to getting back to Vegas.

40:11.880 --> 40:16.590
- I thought you loved the Vegas.
- I do. I do love the Vegas.

40:16.760 --> 40:20.639
Because afterwards,
it is so nice to come home.

40:28.560 --> 40:31.791
- Hi.
- You told my dad?

40:32.320 --> 40:35.039
Your dad found out. He asked me.
I had to tell him the truth.

40:35.200 --> 40:37.475
Oh, so you'll tell my dad the truth,
but you won't tell me?

40:37.640 --> 40:39.119
What are you talking about?

40:40.840 --> 40:44.071
You know what,
maybe you should just ask Theresa.

40:45.760 --> 40:47.591
Just tell me what's going on, okay?

40:50.240 --> 40:51.593
Theresa's pregnant.

41:01.880 --> 41:04.155
And it might not be Eddie's.

41:04.320 --> 41:07.357
So why don't you tell me
what's going on?

